      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The vulnerability is far more severe than a mere 'high' risk; it's an active exploit vector that bypasses standard security layers. Downgrading this to anything less than critical would be an act of professional negligence, and I assure you the board will see through any attempt to minimize this. A full shutdown is the only responsible course of action to prevent a catastrophic, reputation-destroying breach that will far outweigh any temporary SLA penalties.",
