      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The WAF can certainly act as a temporary speed bump, but it is not a permanent fix for a fundamental flaw like this. Relying on a WAF to patch a core SQL injection vulnerability is like putting a band-aid on a structural collapse; it only delays the inevitable. We can certainly manage the *perception* of risk by implementing aggressive monitoring, which I've already initiated, but the underlying threat remains critical until the code is fixed.",
